law.text:
The Department may not require a permit or registration for:
Any machinery or equipment that normally is used in a mobile manner;
Any boiler used exclusively to operate steam engines for farm and domestic use;
The construction of a generating station constructed by a person that is required to obtain a certificate of public convenience and necessity under §§ 7-207 and 7-208 of the Public Utilities Article and regulations adopted by the Public Service Commission;
Actual construction of buildings, apart from any possible emission producing machinery housed in the buildings;
Any parking garage; or
Any parking lot.
